%pyspark

# More documentation on DataFrames can be found at http://spark.apache.org/docs/2.0.2/api/python/pyspark.sql.html

# Read in a CSV into a DataFrame and display it
df = sqlc.read.format("csv").load("/data-sets/new-cs-training3.csv")
df.show() # This is similar to #take, except that prints the results

df.printSchema()

%pyspark

# Read in a CSV into a DataFrame and display it
df = sqlc.read.format("csv").option("inferSchema", True).option("header", True).load("/data-sets/new-cs-training3.csv")
df.show()

%pyspark

# Writing a CSV after re-partitioning will likely cause you to have many files
df.repartition(100).write.format("csv").option("headers", True).save("/data-sets/test.csv")

%pyspark

# A DataFrame is just an RDD with a schema associated with it
rdd = df.rdd
for x in rdd.map(lambda x: list(x)).take(10):
    print x

df.printSchema()

%pyspark

# SELECT some columns from the DataFrame
df.select("age", "DebtRatio").show(2)

# We can also select computations
df.select(df["age"] * 2, df["DebtRatio"] * 100).show(2)

%pyspark

# WHERE and ORDERBY can be used too
df.where(df["age"] == 25).select("age", "DebtRatio").orderBy(df["DebtRatio"].desc()).show()

%pyspark

# We can also replace/add columns
df2 = df.withColumn("DebtRatio", df["DebtRatio"] * 2)
df2.withColumn("Debt", df2["DebtRatio"] * df2["MonthlyIncome"]).select("age", "MonthlyIncome", "DebtRatio", "Debt").show()

%pyspark

# Stats functions
df.describe("age", "DebtRatio", "MonthlyIncome").show()

# Quartiles (quantiles computed for 25%, 50%, and 75%)
for quantile in df.approxQuantile("age", [0.25, 0.5, 0.75], 0.0):
    print quantile

%pyspark

# Create a SQL table that we can use later
df.registerTempTable("training")

%sql

-- We can now refer to this table directly as if we were using SQL Server 2003
SELECT * FROM training ORDER BY account_num DESC LIMIT 100

%sql

-- We can also visualize data
SELECT ROUND(age / 4) * 4 `age`, AVG(DebtRatio) `debt ratio`, AVG(MonthlyIncome) `income` FROM training WHERE MonthlyIncome != -99999 GROUP BY ROUND(age / 4)
